node.text: A few moments from Holi Festival deep in the crowds of Vrindavan (the birth place of Holi) It was so much fun being able to be a part of India’s craziest festival of the year, this is just a quick glimpse of the trip and I’ll be posting some vlog style videos from India real soon so stay tuned! 🙏🏼🇮🇳 Shot and experienced this with 2 legends @jacob @danielsjensen

node.title: Deep inside India’s craziest festival of the year - The Holi Festival 🇮🇳

node.text: Dubrovnik photo dump - I spent one night in the old town of Dubrovnik to experience both parts of the city. I stayed at @villa5db which is located on the main street of the old town (Stradun) just a few minutes walk away from all these photos. I even had views of the whole Stradun street from my window 👌🏼

node.text:
My first time exploring Croatia 🇭🇷
I started my trip here in Dubrovnik, and for two of the nights I stayed up in the cliffs at @villaorabelle - this place had some of the best panoramic views over the coast, and in the whole area 👌🏼 swipe for the beach view 🏖

Busy mornings at @lagavinasagaro
This was the perfect way to spend my last few nights in Spain / Catalonia - 3 nights in S'Agaró at this classic hotel located right by the beach. If you’re planning a trip to Costa Brava, definitely check this place out 👌🏼

node.text:
Barcelona photo dump week one, mostly iPhone shots 🇪🇸
After 3 weeks in Ibiza I needed a detox, so I flew out to BCN last minute to spend a week here eating healthy, getting back into a fitness routine and catching up on work. I love this place so much that I already extended an extra 10 days 🙌🏼
